The standard forms express exclusion grounds and selection criteria in this section as unstructured text. In the introductory note to its [eForms consultation](https://github.com/eForms/eForms), the European Commission had proposed to create an extension to eForms to implement the [European Single Procurement Document (ESPD)](http://ec.europa.eu/growth/single-market/public-procurement/e-procurement/espd/) [Exchange Data Model](https://github.com/ESPD/ESPD-EDM), which expresses this information as structured data, following the model of the [Core Criterion and Core Evidence Vocabulary](https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/solution/core-criterion-and-core-evidence-vocabulary).
